Please use your brain before saying the app sucks and rating it low.  Thanks.

title: Used to be good, now covered in dust.
comment: Although this has always been a rather basic astronomy app, it used to work well and be nice to use. I find the opposite to be true today.  First, there seems to be compass calibration issues, like some other Google apps have had (Maps suffered from this for the longest time). It amazes me that apps developed by Google don't work seamlessly with the Android system - a system developed by Google.  This app also hasn't been updated in over *four years*. Let's see... Four years ago, I was using an HTC Incredible, running Android version Gingerbread (2.3). That was a nice device for the time, but devices have changed in four years. Now I'm on a Samsung Galaxy S4 running Jelly Bean (4.2.2), but many folks are running 4.4 or 5.0 now. As phones and software become more capable, this app will run into more problems.  So, I  say the app is "covered in dust". Sky Map has promise, but won't be useful unless someone maintains it. Until then, more people will shelve it and forget about it.
